Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a drab-coloured pottery vessel, the fabric contains many small white inclusions, the exterior is covered with a cream-coloured slip and slight traces of one line of black-painted hieratic text.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393979) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393979)
